\n<Detective>(There are lockers here too... That girl didn't
like being seen near the lockers...)

The concept of a transcendent being disguised
when discussing the determinism of the future
based on the principle of causality,
'\c[2]Laplace's Demon\c[0]'

The ability to fully grasp and analyze all the
mechanical and physical states that are in effect
at a certain point in time allows for the
definitive knowledge of the entire motion of the
universe, including the future.

And so, it was proposed by the French
mathematician Pierre-Simon Laplace.

\n<Detective>...Surprisingly, that girl is actually good at
studying.
